                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, vivid red.</seg>
                        Scribe: Walda ʾAragāwi. ʾabuna Walda
                        ʾAragāwi is mentioned as the scribe in Additio 1.<date>20th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይቤ፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይቤ፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይብል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; names of King
                           Ḫāyla Śǝllāse, Archbishop Basǝlyos and Bishop Yoḥannǝs; incipit of Text I
                           and its sections; titles of books to be read; two initial lines of some
                           readings in Text II; incipit of the sections of Text III; abbreviations
                           of the directives to the ministers yǝbǝl kahǝn, “the priest says”, yǝbǝl
                           diyaqon, “the deacon says” and yǝbǝl ḥǝzb, “the people say” in Text III;
                           elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals;
                           elements of the quire marks; notes written in the upper margin.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">- <locus target="#5r">5r</locus>: Crude
